# LAMMPS Input File
# Licensed under CC BY 4.0
# A Set of Materials-Science Tutorials for the LAMMPS Simulation Package
# Tutorial 13: phonon dispersion from MD -- vibrational density of states
#
# Record the velocity autocorrelation function (VACF) of the same copper
# crystal at 300 K.  Its Fourier transform is the vibrational density of
# states g(nu) -- the "integral view" of the dispersion curves -- from which
# dos-plot.py also computes the (quantum) harmonic heat capacity.  Uses a
# conventional fcc cell at the 300 K lattice constant, equilibrated with a
# thermostat and sampled in the NVE ensemble so that no thermostat damping
# distorts the spectrum.

variable a0 equal 3.6318          # thermally expanded, as in phonon.lmp
variable T  equal 300.0

units metal
atom_style atomic
boundary p p p

lattice fcc ${a0}
lattice fcc 3.6318
Lattice spacing in x,y,z = 3.6318 3.6318 3.6318
region box block 0 8 0 8 0 8
create_box 1 box
Created orthogonal box = (0 0 0) to (29.0544 29.0544 29.0544)
  1 by 1 by 1 MPI processor grid
create_atoms 1 box
Created 2048 atoms
  using lattice units in orthogonal box = (0 0 0) to (29.0544 29.0544 29.0544)
  create_atoms CPU = 0.000 seconds
mass 1 63.546
pair_style eam/alloy
pair_coeff * * Cu_mishin1.eam.alloy Cu
Reading eam/alloy potential file Cu_mishin1.eam.alloy with DATE: 2007-10-12

# thermalize at T (target 2T initial kinetic energy, half goes potential)
velocity all create $(2.0*v_T) 87287 mom yes rot yes dist gaussian
velocity all create 600 87287 mom yes rot yes dist gaussian
fix nvt all nvt temp ${T} ${T} 0.1
fix nvt all nvt temp 300 ${T} 0.1
fix nvt all nvt temp 300 300 0.1
thermo 500
thermo_style custom step temp pe press
run 5000
Neighbor list info ...
  update: every = 1 steps, delay = 0 steps, check = yes
  max neighbors/atom: 2000, page size: 100000
  master list distance cutoff = 7.50679
  ghost atom cutoff = 7.50679
  binsize = 3.753395, bins = 8 8 8
  1 neighbor lists, perpetual/occasional/extra = 1 0 0
  (1) pair eam/alloy, perpetual
      attributes: half, newton on
      pair build: half/bin/atomonly/newton
      stencil: half/bin/3d
      bin: standard
